HEADWORD: disenfranchised
<hw>disenfranchised</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>deprived of the rights of
citizenship, especially the right to vote. Opposite of
<ant>enfranchised</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> disfranchised, voteless.</syn>⟦br⟧
